tore my ligaments.

125
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,880
-So, you picked yoga.
-Yeah.

126
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:56,320
Not too light for you?

127
00:08:57,520 --> 00:09:00,960
Actually, on the contrary,
it's quite difficult.

128
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:04,000
Yoga changes your body and your mind.

129
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,720
Don't you find
doing it every day monotonous?

130
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:07,640
Well...

131
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:11,000
that's how you become an expert. So...

132
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:14,720
Plus, now I don't have
to do 80 kilograms squats.

133
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:19,440
Fair enough. Okay.

134
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,760
Let's do this.

135
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:22,280
Three minute plank.

136
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,360
Let's go.

137
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:32,320
Could we make it two minutes
and 56 seconds please?

138
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,440
Because I've never crossed
two minutes and 57 seconds

139
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:37,520
and I don't wanna lose self-respect.

140
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,760
-All right.
-What?

141
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:44,960
Your truth bombs. I'm not used to them.

142
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,840
Should I keep going...

143
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,480
-You can get up.
-Okay.

144
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:51,520
Last question. Why yoga?

145
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:55,760
Because it is better
than being addicted to selfies,

146
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:58,080
or junk food, or alcohol, or drugs.

147
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,080
-You were an addict?
-Yeah.

148
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,640
What was your drug of choice?

149
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,760
Everything.

150
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:11,360
When I didn't get selected
for Nationals, I...

151
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:16,760
smoke, shoot, snort, pop, fuck, eat,

152
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:19,520
I mean, you name it, I did it.

153
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,240
Okay.

154
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,520
Welcome to Umami.

155
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:29,520
Break a leg.

156
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,200
Thanks.

157
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:34,600
Great.

158
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,600
<i>So, tell me, who is Dhananjay Deshpande?</i>

159
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:44,880
Why don't you tell me?

160
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:50,120
Four generations ago, your grandfather
was a well-known politician of India.

161
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:53,080
Then politics became your family business.

162
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,880
You're privileged. Entitled.

163
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,320
You don't date Indian women.

164
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:05,320
There was a girl,
from the royal family of Kewad, right?

165
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:12,160
You're so far removed from the real India.

166
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,840
Actually, you have no idea

167
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:17,800
about the day-to-day struggles
of a common man.

168
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:21,240
-Is that how you see me?
-That's how everyone here sees you.

169
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:23,200
That's not how I want to be seen.

170
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:25,120
Fair enough. So, you tell me.

171
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:29,120
In your opinion,
who is Dhananjay Deshpande?

172
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:38,520
Sometimes, his father's son,

173
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:41,640
or his grandfather's grandson.

174
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:46,560
A boy who went to an elite boarding school
in the hills.

175
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:52,520
Who saw his family
only in the summer vacations.

176
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,680
Who was bullied.

177
00:11:56,400 --> 00:12:00,360
So, that boy had to pretend to be strong

178
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,440
and face those bullies.

179
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:07,640
And I think, I'm still that boy.

180
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:11,560
A boy pretending to be a man
who's pretending to be strong

181
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,000
and facing his bullies.

182
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:17,640
Who didn't want to be a politician,
but an architect.

183
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:20,520
I loved drawing.

184
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,600
I still do, in fact.

185
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:28,480
But all that said, now that I'm here,

186
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:31,480
I wanna do the best I can.

187
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:35,440
Because when the going gets tough,
I stick around.

188
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,400
It's an old habit.

189
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:41,160
Who do you see in the mirror?

190
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:43,480
I'm not a good son.

191
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,400
I just pretend to be.

192
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:50,960
I listen to my father
but I don't understand what he says.

193
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:58,000
Some of his party's decisions
leave me fuming.

194
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:04,320
What is his worst quality?

195
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,280
That he lives in an echo chamber.

196
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,800
He genuinely can't take criticism.

197
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:13,680
Whatever I am,
I'm willing and able to learn.

198
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,000
And I want to learn.

199
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,920
We can work with this.

200
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:26,040
New guard versus old guard.
It's always good.

201
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:30,320
Wow... I feel naked.

202
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,880
Stripped and whipped.

203
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,160
But today was good. Thank you.

204
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:41,080
I will take your leave.

205
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:49,560
Hey.

206
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:52,880
